Parliament, Friday, 26 June 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services has postponed the two meetings it had planned for today. The committee was meant to receive a progress report on investigations by the Special Investigating Unit (SIU) into matters referred to it concerning the Department of Justice and Constitutional Development. The committee was also to be briefed on mechanisms in place to facilitate co-operation between the SIU and the National Prosecuting Authority.
	
	In the evening, the committee was meant to receive a briefing on the operationalisation of the Protection of Information Act and capacitation/resourcing of the Information Regulator, as well as a briefing on preparation for the transfer of Promotion of Access to Information Act powers and functions to the information Regulator.
	
